-------- Original Message --------
Subject: 	[PATCH] doc: respect --htmldir
Date: 	Tue, 24 Jan 2012 21:13:52 -0500
From: 	Mike Frysinger <vapier@...65...>
To: 	nicolas@...1...



The configure script already sets up $(htmldir) for us (which the user
can override), so just use that rather than hardcoding our own path.

Signed-off-by: Mike Frysinger <vapier@...65...>
---
 doc/Makefile.am |    1 -
 1 files changed, 0 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/doc/Makefile.am b/doc/Makefile.am
index 09b8eb5..1e8aa14 100644
--- a/doc/Makefile.am
+++ b/doc/Makefile.am
@@ -2,7 +2,6 @@ XSLTPROC=@XSLTPROC@
 XSLTPROC_FLAGS=@XSLTPROC_FLAGS@
 XHTML_STYLESHEET=style.xsl
 
-htmldir = $(prefix)/share/doc/@PACKAGE@/html
 dist_html_DATA = html/*
 EXTRA_DIST = main.xml gpl.xml install.xml about.xml report.xml supportedgc.xml supportedmonitors.xml thanks.xml techdocs.xml usage.xml style.xsl style-fo.xsl
 
-- 
1.7.8.3




